            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~RKThoadan" class="author" title="author name and user ID">RKThoadan (89437) </a> | about 5 months ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=4857627&cid=46397081">(#46397081)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_46397081" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="2" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>I don't think it's possible to make something "illegal tender", at least in the US. If I want to trade you one thing for another thing, it's hard to see the government saying we can't do that. "legal tender" is something that <strong>must</strong> be accepted for all debts, public and private. Trying to say that something cannot be used even in barter, is pretty tricky.</p></div>
