    <div id="comment_46396935">
        <header data-points="2" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:You can't make tech safe from malice"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:You can't make tech safe from malice<span> (2)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~jythie" class="author" title="author name and user ID">jythie (914043) </a> | about 5 months ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=4857627&cid=46396935">(#46396935)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_46396935" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="2" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body">To be fair, with autonomous cars, they do not need to be perfect, just more reliable then human drivers.  Given we have pretty good metrics on how often people mess up, there is a pretty clear bar afterwhich autonomous cars are 'good enough'.</div>
