            <div class="comment-body"><p>I would put it past them.  This is incredibly small potatoes for them.  I know a lot of the bitcoin apologists think they're doing something incredibly revolutionary.  They aren't.  Basic economics says this is bound to failure because there is a fixed amount of coins to be mined.  That's a very bad feature of a currency (works great for an investment, though one will always need to find the next fool)</p><p>Maybe organized crime is involved or maybe a couple of 8th graders.  I really don't know, nor do I care.  I'm just basking in the shadenfreude at this point.</p></div>
